-- Copper Advances for a Third Day in London, Shanghai, New York on Recovery
-- B y   G l e n y s   S i m
-- 2010-12-21T01:07:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-21/copper-advances-for-a-third-day-in-london-shanghai-new-york-on-recovery.html
Copper advanced for a third day from
London to Shanghai on optimism the economic recovery in the U.S.
remains on track, boosting the demand outlook for the metal used
in construction and household appliances.  The metal for three-month delivery on the London Metal
Exchange rose as much as 0.3 percent to $9,230 a metric ton, and
traded at $9,218 by 9:06 a.m. Singapore time.  Copper for March-delivery on the Shanghai Futures Exchange
gained as much as 1 percent to 69,300 yuan a ton, and futures on
the Comex in New York added as much as 0.3 percent to $4.2185 a
pound.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Glenys Sim at 
 gsim4@bloomberg.net  